  "prompt": "What's a good way to retain more of what you read?",
  "response": "Here are several effective strategies to improve reading retention:\n\n1. Active Reading Techniques\n- Take notes while reading\n- Highlight key passages\n- Summarize main points after each section\n- Ask yourself questions about the material\n\n2. Mental Engagement Methods\n- Relate new information to things you already know\n- Visualize the content\n- Discuss what you've read with others\n- Teach the material to someone else\n\n3. Comprehension Strategies\n- Read slowly and deliberately\n- Break complex texts into smaller sections\n- Pause and reflect periodically\n- Use context clues to understand difficult concepts\n\n4. Memory Reinforcement\n- Review notes within 24 hours of reading\n- Create mind maps or visual summaries\n- Use spaced repetition techniques\n- Write a brief reflection after reading\n\n5. Physical Approaches\n- Read when you're most alert\n- Minimize distractions\n- Use a physical bookmark to track progress\n- Take short breaks to maintain focus\n\n6. Technological Aids\n- Use reading apps with annotation features\n- Try digital flashcard tools\n- Record audio summaries\n- Use text-to-speech for additional comprehension\n\nExperiment with different techniques to find what works best for you.",
